                </p>
                <p>
                    Finding the perpendicular height.

                </p>
                <p>
                    We use pythagorean relationship that is <me>H^2=b^2+h^2</me>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> h^2=\amp H^2-b^2 </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp 5^2=3^2</mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp 25-9 </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp 16 </mrow>
                        <mrow>\sqrt{h^2}= \amp \sqrt{16} </mrow>
                        <mrow>h= \amp 4\,cm </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                
                <p>
                    Finding <m>\text{tan} \theta</m>
                </p>
