                <mrow> tan \, \theta=\amp \frac{\text{Opposite}}{\text{Adjacent}} =\amp \frac{BC}{AB}</mrow>
                <mrow> cos\, \theta =\amp \frac{\text{Adjacent}}{\text{Hypotenuse}}=\amp \frac{AB}{AC}</mrow>
                <mrow> sin\,\theta =\amp \frac{\text{Opposite}}{\text{Hypotenuse}}=\amp \frac{BC}{AC}</mrow>
                
            </md>
        </p>
        <p>
            <term>The above formulas applies also for the trigonometric ratios for</term> <m>\alpha</m>.
